
// This Hyperlambda code snippet replaces occurrences of a placeholder string within a node's value. It first targets the [.result] node using [set-value] and then applies [strings.replace] to substitute the placeholder "[[recaptcha]]" with the actual value retrieved from the [.captcha] node using [get-value]. The operation updates the [.result] node with the modified string.
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      .:[[recaptcha]]
      get-value:x:@.captcha
